{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"BrazeKit"}],"title":"Apple Push Certificate"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you can send a push notification using Braze, you must provide your Push notification file or certificate from Apple. You may present either a "},{"code":".p8","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file (recommended) or a ","type":"text"},{"code":".p12","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" certificate."}]},{"text":".p8 File (recommended)","anchor":"p8-File-recommended","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As described on this "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/help.apple.com\/developer-account\/#\/devcdfbb56a3","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your developer account, go to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/certificate","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under Keys, select All and click the Add button (+) in the upper-right corner."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under Key Description, enter a unique name for the signing key."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Under Key Services, select the APNs checkbox, then click Continue. Click ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirm"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note the Key ID. Click "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" to generate and download the key now."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you download the key, it is saved as a text file with a .p8 file extension. Save the file in a secure place because the key is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not saved in your developer account and you won’t be able to download it again"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/dashboard-01.braze.com\/app_settings\/app_settings","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" page in the dashboard and upload the .p8 file.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When prompted, also enter your app’s ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/identifier\/bundle\/"},{"type":"text","text":", the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/ios\/authkey","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that you noted when generating the key, and your "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/#\/membership","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Click "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Save","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"p12-Certificate-legacy","level":3,"text":".p12 Certificate (legacy)"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you may utilize Apple’s older authentication scheme (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"type":"text","text":" SSL certificates). Unlike the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"type":"text","text":" solution described above, these certificates automatically expire every year and will require you to regenerate and re-upload them. Braze will send you email reminders as the certificate approaches expiration to help your notifications continue uninterrupted, but because this is a manual process we recommend utilizing the above-described "},{"code":".p8","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" authentication scheme instead. However, if you still wish to, you may configure and upload ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"text":" certificates as described here:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-1-Generate-Certificate-Signing-Request","level":4,"text":"Step 1: Generate Certificate Signing Request","type":"heading"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/ios\/manage\/overview\/index.action","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Select ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Identifiers"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" in the left sidebar and filter ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"App Ids"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" using the button on the right of the page "},{"identifier":"apns-certificate-identifiers-app-ids.png","type":"image"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select your application."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enable push notifications by checking the checkbox then click ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Edit"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"apns-certificate-app-id-config.png","type":"image"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click Create Certificate under the Production SSL Certificate "},{"identifier":"apns-certificate-modal.png","type":"image"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Production SSL Certificate"}]},{"text":" are suitable for App Store and TestFlight builds. Use a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Development SSL Certificate","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" to for development builds."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow the instructions from the SSL certificate assistant."}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must update your provisioning profile for the app after you create your SSL certificates. A simple “Refresh” in the organizer will accomplish this."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"level":4,"anchor":"Step-2-Export-Certificate","type":"heading","text":"Step 2: Export Certificate"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download the production push certificate that you just created and open it with the Keychain Access application."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In Keychain Access, click on My Certificates and locate your push certificate.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Export it as a "},{"code":".p12","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file and use a temporary, unsecure password (you will need this password when uploading your certificate to Braze)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/dashboard-01.braze.com\/app_settings\/app_settings","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Settings","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Settings"}]},{"text":" page in the dashboard and upload your production certificate. ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-upload.png"}]}]}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can upload either your development or production push ce